race.comment: STRANDED (7) never looked likely first-up in town but has taken the right steps since, showing solid improvement in his last two. Draws to get the gun run from the inside alley and picks up the key booking of Toeroek. Looks ready to break through. KAPPA CRUCIS (5) has contested two strong maidens to kick off his career and has been doing his best work late on each occasion. Will likely get back again from the wide draw but the rise in trip suits and he'll be launching late. CORNERBACK (4) was sound without threatening in his stable debut. Keeps Holder and is expected to take improvement from that run. Capable of giving this a shake. QATAR (6) jumped out well before his first-up run in town but couldn't make an impression behind a smart winner. Fitter now and better placed in this easier assignment. CAER IBORMEITH (8) was a flashing light late last start, closing off strongly into a midfield finish. Draws far kinder this time and can play a major role.
